  <diagram id="page2" name="Notes &amp; Log">
    <mxGraphModel dx="1622" dy="900" grid="0" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="1600" pageHeight="2000" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="0" />
        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />

        <mxCell id="hdr" value="Wearable ROM Tracker — Research &amp; Decision Log" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=22;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#26215C;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="200" y="20" width="1200" height="44" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="hdr2" value="Last updated: June 28, 2026" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=13;fontColor=#888780;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="200" y="60" width="1200" height="24" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

        <!-- Market Research block -->
        <mxCell id="n1h" value="Market Research — Jun 22, 2026" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=#993C1D;fillColor=#FAECE7;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=14;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#712B13;rounded=1;spacingLeft=12;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="110" width="460" height="36" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="n1b" value="• No consumer product tracks joint-specific ROM for gym use&#xa;• Clinical trackers (Xsens DOT, Kinetisense) target labs and PT clinics&#xa;• Hinge Health: sensors + AI vision + clinical care team for rehab&#xa;• Athos: tracks EMG (muscle activation), not joint angles — different problem&#xa;• Technogym Biodrive: tracks angle, force curve, velocity, limb symmetry&#xa;  — 6 resistance types: isotonic, eccentric, viscous, elastic, no-inertia, eccentric overload&#xa;  — Most features replicable with 2x IMUs per joint&#xa;  — MyWellness Cloud: longitudinal tracking across connected equipment&#xa;• SyncKnee (2025 research): angle + swelling tracking — not a product yet&#xa;• MagDot (academic): ±2.72° elbow, ±4.14° knee, ±4.61° shoulder accuracy&#xa;• KEY INSIGHT: consumer gap is real — IMU tech is mature and cheap&#xa;• Best entry point: single-joint sleeve, knee (squat/cycling) or shoulder (press)" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=#F5C4B3;fillColor=#FAECE7;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=11;fontColor=#712B13;rounded=1;spacingLeft=12;spacingTop=10;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="148" width="460" height="260" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

        <!-- Hardware block -->
        <mxCell id="n2h" value="Hardware — Jun 22, 2026" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=#0F6E56;fillColor=#E1F5EE;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=14;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#085041;rounded=1;spacingLeft=12;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="540" y="110" width="460" height="36" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="n2b" value="• Microcontrollers considered: ESP32, Arduino Nano 33 BLE Sense, nRF52840&#xa;• IMUs considered: MPU-6050 (6-axis), BNO055 (9-axis, onboard fusion), ICM-42688&#xa;• CHOSEN: 2x Seeed XIAO nRF52840 Sense (~$16 each)&#xa;  — Smallest dev board in class: 21x17.5mm&#xa;  — Built-in LSM6DS3 IMU + BLE radio&#xa;  — Built-in LiPo charging circuit (no extra hardware needed)&#xa;  — Same nRF52840 chip used in production fitness wearables&#xa;  — Direct path to custom PCB when ready&#xa;• 2x LiPo 150mAh JST batteries (~$5 each)&#xa;• Mounting: elastic armband or velcro + athletic tape for PoC&#xa;• TOTAL KIT COST: ~$50 for both boards + batteries&#xa;• PoC: Bicep curl — one sensor upper arm, one lower arm&#xa;  — Angle between two quaternions = elbow ROM" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=#9FE1CB;fillColor=#E1F5EE;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=11;fontColor=#085041;rounded=1;spacingLeft=12;spacingTop=10;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="540" y="148" width="460" height="260" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

        <!-- Firmware block -->
        <mxCell id="n3h" value="Firmware — Jun 22, 2026" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=#0F6E56;fillColor=#E1F5EE;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=14;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#085041;rounded=1;spacingLeft=12;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="440" width="460" height="36" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="n3b" value="• Core loop: read IMU → compute angle delta → detect rep → stream over BLE&#xa;• Rep detection: flex past 120° then return below 30° = 1 complete rep&#xa;• Track min/max ROM per rep for performance scoring&#xa;• Eccentric vs concentric: detectable via angle direction + velocity&#xa;• Deep sleep duty cycle (key for battery life):&#xa;  — Active draw (BLE + IMU): 7–15 mA&#xa;  — Idle: 1–3 mA&#xa;  — Deep sleep: 5 µA (0.005 mA)&#xa;  — 150mAh battery = ~12 hours active use&#xa;  — Wake every 10ms during set, sleep between sets&#xa;  — Same duty cycle approach as WHOOP and Fitbit&#xa;• BLE GATT: custom UUID, notify characteristic&#xa;  — Packet format: [angle_float, rep_int, timestamp_ms]&#xa;• Sensor fusion: accelerometer + gyroscope + magnetometer" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=#9FE1CB;fillColor=#E1F5EE;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=11;fontColor=#085041;rounded=1;spacingLeft=12;spacingTop=10;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="478" width="460" height="280" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

        <!-- App block -->
        <mxCell id="n4h" value="Mobile App — Jun 22, 2026" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=#854F0B;fillColor=#FAEEDA;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=14;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#633806;rounded=1;spacingLeft=12;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="540" y="440" width="460" height="36" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="n4b" value="• Platform options:&#xa;  — MIT App Inventor: no-code, fastest PoC (days to working app)&#xa;  — Flutter + flutter_blue: cross-platform, best for production&#xa;  — React Native + BLE Manager: good for web developers&#xa;  — Swift (iOS) / Kotlin (Android): native, most control&#xa;• Core MVP features:&#xa;  — BLE scan, connect, auto-reconnect on open&#xa;  — Subscribe to GATT angle + rep notifications&#xa;  — Live real-time line chart of elbow angle over time&#xa;  — Show min/max ROM per rep as horizontal reference lines&#xa;  — Large rep count display with set timer&#xa;  — End session → summary: avg ROM, best ROM, total reps&#xa;• Future: form alert when ROM drops below personal baseline&#xa;• Future: longitudinal history charts across sessions" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=#FAC775;fillColor=#FAEEDA;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=11;fontColor=#633806;rounded=1;spacingLeft=12;spacingTop=10;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="540" y="478" width="460" height="280" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>


        <!-- Firmware Progress block -->
        <mxCell id="n7h" value="Firmware Progress &#x2014; Jun 28, 2026" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=#0F6E56;fillColor=#E1F5EE;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=14;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#085041;rounded=1;spacingLeft=12;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="1040" y="110" width="460" height="36" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="n7b" value="&#x2022; Step 1: IMU read &#x2014; LSM6DS3 accel &#x2192; simplified quaternion &#x2192; Serial print&#xa;  &#x2014; Confirmed: w&#x2248;1.0 flat, x/y change on tilt, z=0&#xa;&#x2022; Step 2: Elbow angle calc &#x2014; hardcoded ref quat + live sensor&#xa;  &#x2014; computeAngle(): q_rel = q1_conj * q2, angle = 2*acos(rw)*180/pi&#xa;  &#x2014; Confirmed: 0 deg flat, 90 deg at right angle&#xa;&#x2022; Step 3: Two boards over BLE (Bluefruit library)&#xa;  &#x2014; Peripheral (forearm): quaternion broadcast at 50Hz&#xa;  &#x2014; Central (upper arm): receives forearm quat, computes angle&#xa;  &#x2014; Confirmed: 90 and 180 deg match real positions wirelessly&#xa;&#x2022; Library fixes: deleted Arduino_LSM6DS3, switched ArduinoBLE to Bluefruit&#xa;&#x2022; Measures: sagittal + frontal planes | Ignores: transverse (qz=0)&#xa;&#x2022; Next: rep detection, Flutter iOS app, arm mounting" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=#9FE1CB;fillColor=#E1F5EE;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=11;fontColor=#085041;rounded=1;spacingLeft=12;spacingTop=10;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="1040" y="148" width="460" height="240" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

        <!-- V2 block -->
        <mxCell id="n5h" value="V2 &amp; Future — Jun 22, 2026" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=#534AB7;fillColor=#EEEDFE;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=14;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#3C3489;rounded=1;spacingLeft=12;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="790" width="960" height="36" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="n5b" value="• Smart sleeve: single-joint targeting (knee for squats/cycling, shoulder for pressing)&#xa;• Custom PCB: nRF52840 chip — same as XIAO, direct path from dev board&#xa;• Expand exercises: squat depth (knee angle), shoulder press ROM, deadlift hip hinge&#xa;• Force estimation: add force sensor OR estimate from IMU acceleration + known weight&#xa;• Haptic feedback: buzz device when ROM drops below threshold (bad form)&#xa;• Accuracy validation target: within ±5° vs clinical goniometer&#xa;• Textile sensor approach (SyncKnee-style): poly(SBS) fiber + EGaIn alloy for sleeve integration&#xa;• Cloud sync (MyWellness-style): longitudinal ROM tracking across sessions and exercises&#xa;• Asymmetry detection: compare left vs right sensor readings per rep" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=#AFA9EC;fillColor=#EEEDFE;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=11;fontColor=#3C3489;rounded=1;spacingLeft=12;spacingTop=10;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="828" width="960" height="200" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

        <!-- Next Steps block -->
        <mxCell id="n6h" value="Next Steps / Open Tasks" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=#444441;fillColor=#F1EFE8;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=14;fontStyle=1;fontColor=#2C2C2A;rounded=1;spacingLeft=12;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="1060" width="960" height="36" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="n6b" value="[x] Order 2x Seeed XIAO nRF52840 Sense + 2x LiPo 150mAh JST (~$50 total)&#xa;[ ] Choose mounting solution (sleeve, velcro, or elastic armband)&#xa;[x] Set up Arduino IDE + Seeed nRF52 board package + LSM6DS3 IMU library&#xa;[x] Write firmware: read quaternions → compute elbow angle delta → print to serial&#xa;[ ] Implement rep counter: detect flex/extension cycle (>120° then &lt;30°)&#xa;[ ] Implement deep sleep duty cycle between sets (target 5µA idle)&#xa;[x] Implement BLE (Bluefruit): peripheral streams quat, central computes angle&#xa;[ ] Choose app platform (MIT App Inventor for speed / Flutter for production)&#xa;[ ] Build live angle graph in app (real-time line chart)&#xa;[ ] Build rep counter display + session summary screen&#xa;[ ] Validate accuracy vs goniometer (target ±5°)&#xa;[ ] Expand to second exercise (squat depth or shoulder press)" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=#D3D1C7;fillColor=#F1EFE8;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=11;fontColor=#444441;rounded=1;spacingLeft=12;spacingTop=10;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="40" y="1098" width="960" height="230" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

      </root>
    </mxGraphModel>
  </diagram>
  <diagram id="page3" name="Learning Resources">
    <mxGraphModel dx="1622" dy="900" grid="0" gridSize="10" guides="1" tooltips="1" connect="1" arrows="1" fold="1" page="1" pageScale="1" pageWidth="3000" pageHeight="2200" math="0" shadow="0">
      <root>
        <mxCell id="0" />
        <mxCell id="1" parent="0" />

        <!-- TITLE -->
        <mxCell id="title" value="Learning Resources — Wearable ROM Tracker" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=0;fontStyle=1;fontSize=22;fontColor=#26215C;" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="600" y="30" width="1200" height="50" as="geometry" />
